{{Zoroastrianism}}
'''Asman''' is the [[Avestan language|Avestan]] and [[Middle Persian]] name of the [[Zoroastrianism|Zoroastrian]] divinity that is the hypostasis of the sky. Asman is the "highest heaven," and is distinguished from the firmament (''thwasha''), which lies nearer the earth. The 27th day of the [[Zoroastrian calendar]] is dedicated to him.

In the [[Avesta]], specifically in the [[Vendidad]], the word is mentioned as being the first thing created. The word is also the origination of the word (آسمان) ''aasmaan'' in modern [[Persian language|Persian]], [[Urdu]] and [[Pashto language|Pashto]] as well as (ਅਸਮਾਨ) ''asmaan'' in [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]], (आसमान) in [[Hindi]] and (আসমান) in [[Bengali language|Bengali]].<ref>{{harvnb|Gershevitch|Fisher|1985|p=642}}</ref>

