{{for|the comic by Al Columbia|The Blood-Clot Boy}} '''Blood Clot Boy''' is a figure in the [[mythology|mythologies]] of several [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] tribes, including the [[Cree]], [[Blackfoot]], [[Pawnee people|Pawnee]], and [[Arapaho]]. He is depicted as being born from a [[Thrombus|clot of blood]].[http://www.ruthenia.ru/folklore/berezkin/eng/061_66.htm]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/BloodClotBoy-Blackfoot.html |title=Blood Clot Boy |work=First People of America and Canada}}</ref>
