'''Santiago María García de la Rasilla Domínguez''' (18 October 1936 &ndash; 13 August 2018) was a Spanish-born Peruvian [[Roman Catholic]] bishop. García de la Rasilla Domínuez was born in Spain and was ordained to the priesthood in Spain for the [[Society of Jesus]]. He served as titular bishop of ''Voncaria.'' From 2006 to 2014, he served as bishop of the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Jaén in Peru]] in [[Peru]].<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/jaen1.htm Apostolic Vicariate of Jaen in Peru] [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref><ref>[http://mfc-peru.blogspot.com/2012/11/visita-de-los-presidentes-nacionales-al.html VISITA DE LOS PRESIDENTES NACIONALES AL OBISPO DEL VICARIATO DE JAEN] {{es icon}}</ref>

