In [[demonology]], '''Xezbeth''' (alternately '''Shezbeth''') is a [[demon]] of lies and legends, who invents untrue tales. Its name in Arabic is "The Liar" ({{lang-ar|الكذّاب}} ''al-Kadhāb'').<ref>{{cite book | authorlink = Jan Knappert | last = Knappert | first = Jan | title = The Encyclopaedia of Middle Eastern Mythology and Religion | year = 1993 | page = 256 | url = https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=9ooYAAAAIAAJ}}</ref>

According to French occultist [[Collin de Plancy]]'s ''[[Dictionnaire Infernal]]'' (1853), it is impossible to count the number of its disciples.<ref>{{cite book | authorlink = Collin de Plancy | last = Collin de Plancy | first = Jacques Auguste Simon | title = Dictionnaire infernal: ou Répertoire universel des êtres, des personnages | year = 1853 | page = 536 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=ng8JAAAAQAAJ}}</ref>

